This paper deals with fashion recognition using deep convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also involves multi-task learning, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.MM). The proposed model uses knowledge sharing strategies, which is a common technique in deep learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves classification and attribute prediction, which are common tasks in information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
